$ SQL: trigger
@ trigger

A trigger specifies a series of actions to be executed when one of the following SQL operations are executed on a → development/databases/SQL/table:
  • → development/databases/SQL/DML/insert[`insert`]
  • `delete`
  • `update`

The trigger has an *action time* that specifies *when* the sequence of actions are executed. Possible values are
  • `before`
  • `after`
  • `instead of`
